  <h1>Dedicated Circuits</h1>
  <p>
    Dedicated circuits protect high-demand equipment, reduce nuisance tripping,
    and support safer operation for modern electrical loads. We design and
    install circuits sized for the equipment you actually use.
  </p>

  <h2>When dedicated circuits are needed</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Adding EV chargers, workshop tools, or major appliances</li>
    <li>Recurring breaker trips on shared branch circuits</li>
    <li>Expanding electrical use in garages, additions, or outbuildings</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What Top Tier Electrical provides</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Circuit sizing and route planning</li>
    <li>Panel connection and labeling updates</li>
    <li>Code-aware installation and testing</li>
    <li>Clear scope and upgrade recommendations if required</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Related services</h2>
  <p>
    Some dedicated-circuit projects pair with
    <a href="/panel-upgrades">panel upgrades</a> and
    <a href="/ev-chargers">EV charger installs</a>. Compare services on
    <a href="/services">our services hub</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>FAQ</h2>
  <details>
    <summary>Can one dedicated circuit support multiple devices?</summary>
    <p>
      Generally no for major loads; we recommend dedicated circuits sized for
      each qualifying device to avoid overload risk.
    </p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Do you install dedicated circuits for garages and shops?</summary>
    <p>
      Yes. We commonly add dedicated circuits for workshops, detached garages,
      and equipment-specific applications.
    </p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Will you label and document new circuits?</summary>
    <p>
      Yes. We provide clear panel labeling and explain what each new circuit
      supports.
    </p>
  </details>

